<subSubSection pageId="137" pageNumber="138" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="137" pageNumber="138">
112b. 
<taxonomicName LSID="4D0003FB-F451-5C97-AB73-A3989BBE7F02" authority="Sa'ad, Meded. Bot. Mus. Herb. Rijks Univ. Utrecht 281: 191. 1967. (Sa'ad 1967: 191)." authorityName="Sa'ad, Meded. Bot. Mus. Herb. Rijks Univ. Utrecht 281: 191. 1967. (Sa'ad" authorityYear="1967" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus pilosellifolius subsp. var. var. linearifolius" order="Solanales" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="pilosellifolius" subSpecies="var." variety="linearifolius">
Convolvulus pilosellifolius var. linearifolius 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sa’ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
, Meded. Bot. Mus. Herb. Rijks Univ. Utrecht 281: 191. 1967. (
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sa’ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
1967: 191).
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="137" pageNumber="138" type="type">
<paragraph pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="137" pageNumber="138">
IRAN, Bushehr, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Koie</emphasis>
268 (holotype B).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="137" pageNumber="138" type="distinguishing features">
<paragraph pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Distinguishing features.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="137" pageNumber="138">This is a delicate form with linear-lanceolate leaves to 2 cm wide and mostly solitary flowers.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="137" pageNumber="138" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="137" pageNumber="138">
The occasional specimen of this variety occurs throughout most of the range of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Desr., Encycl. [Lamarck et al.] 3: 551. 1792. (Desrousseaux" authorityYear="1792" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus pilosellifolius" order="Solanales" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pilosellifolius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Convolvulus pilosellifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but especially around the Arabian/Persian Gulf, such as 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Good</emphasis>
193 from Bahrain.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="137" pageNumber="138" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="137" pageNumber="138">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Desr., Encycl. [Lamarck et al.] 3: 551. 1792. (Desrousseaux" authorityYear="1792" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus pilosellifolius" order="Solanales" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pilosellifolius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Convolvulus pilosellifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be confused with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L., Sp. Pl. 1: 158. 1753. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus cantabrica" order="Solanales" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cantabrica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Convolvulus cantabrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, especially forms of that species previously assigned to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus linearis" order="Solanales" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Convolvulus linearis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in the shorter corolla (to 15 mm) and glabrous ovary and capsule.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
